Package edu.nyu.cs.javagit.api.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CommandResponse
    Marker interface for git command response objects.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GitAdd
    GitAdd provides an interface for adding files or directory tree into git repository
    GitAddOptions
    A class to manage passing add options to the GitAdd command.
    GitAddResponse
    Response data object obtained from git-add command.
    GitAddResponse.ResponseString
    For saving errors, warnings and comments related information in the response object.
    GitBranch
    GitBranch provides an API for git-branch operation in a git repository.
    GitBranchOptions
    A class to manage passing branch options to the GitBranch command.
    GitBranchResponse
    A response data object for the git-branch command.
    GitBranchResponse.BranchRecord
    A record containing branch, its head SHA1, and the comment of the commit on head.
    GitCheckout
    GitCheckout provides an interface for checking out files from a particular branch in the repository or creating a new branch and switching to it.
    GitCheckoutOptions
    Class for managing options for <git-checkout> command.
    GitCheckoutResponse
    Response data object for <git-checkout> command.
    GitClone
    GitClone provides an API for git-clone operation on a repository.
    GitCloneOptions
    A class to manage passing options to the GitClone command.
    GitCloneResponse  
    GitCommit
    GitCommit provides an API to commit changes to a git repository.
    GitCommitOptions
    A class to manage passing commit arguments to the GitCommit command.
    GitCommitResponse
    A response data object for the git-commit command.
    GitCommitResponse.AddedOrDeletedFile
    Represents a file added to or deleted from the repository for a given commit.
    GitCommitResponse.CopiedOrMovedFile
    Represents a file that was copied from an existing file already tracked in the repository or a tracked file that was moved from one name/place to another.
    GitInit  
    GitInitOptions  
    GitInitResponse  
    GitLog
    GitLog provides an interface to retrieve logs from a git repository
    GitLogOptions  
    GitLogResponse
    A response data object for the git log command.
    GitLogResponse.Commit
    A data structure which holds information about each commit.
    GitLogResponse.CommitFile
    This class hold information about a file affected by a commit
    GitLogResponse.ResponseString  
    GitMv
    GitMv provides an interface to move files, symlinks or directories to a different location or rename them.
    GitMvOptions
    A class to manage options to the GitMv command.
    GitMvResponse
    A response data object for the git-mv command.
    GitReset
    GitReset provides an API to perform git-reset functionality against a git repository: reset the current HEAD to the specified state.
    GitResetOptions
    A class to manage passing arguments to the GitReset command.
    GitResetResponse
    A response data object for the git-reset command.
    GitRm
    GitRm provides an interface to remove files from a git repository.
    GitRmOptions
    A class to manage passing arguments to the GitRm command.
    GitRmResponse
    GitRmResponse holds the response information returned by the GitRm class.
    GitStatus
    GitStatus provides an API to status of a git repository.
    GitStatusOptions
    A class for managing options and passing these options to <git-status> command.
    GitStatusResponse
    A response data object for <git-status> command
    GitStatusResponse.ErrorDetails  
    GitStatusResponse.IterableIterator<T>
    An inner class for converting an iterator to iterable object.
